gov.nih.nlm.meme.sql
Class DataWriterConstraints

java.lang.Object
  gov.nih.nlm.meme.sql.DataWriterConstraints
public class DataWriterConstraints
extends Object

Parameter container for the DataWriter. Allows you to specify things like the columns to read, whether or not to select default, how to join multiple tables, and what additional handling should be performed before writing to the file.

Field Detail

field_separator

public char field_separator
The fields in the file will be separated by the field_separator. The default value is '|'. If it is different, one has to set this parameter.

truncate

public boolean truncate
Indicates if the file gets overwritten or if the new lines get appended to the end of the file. The default value is true.

distinct

public boolean distinct
Indicates if all or only all distinct lines get written out. The default is that only distinct lines get written out.

fields_to_write

public OrderedHashMap fields_to_write
Fields of the table which should be written out (if one chooses to not write out every field ot to write them out in another order). The fields get written out in the order of the ArrayList.

public OrderedHashMap defaults
If there are default values that should get written out the same in every line (without looking it up in the data source), these values can

order

public OrderedHashMap order
For example order.put("rank", "DESC") or order.put("cui_1"); order.put("cui_2")

conditions

public String[] conditions
This is used to give conditions which have to be met by the data. For example, 
   table_names = new String[] {"mrd_classes", "mrd_concepts"};
   conditions = new String[] {"mrd_classes.cui = mrd_concepts.cui",
                              "mrd_concepts.status = 'R'", "mrd_classes.expiration_date IS NULL"};
